er frequency holds, with an\naverage stress drop of $\\Delta\\sigma$ = 2.1 +- 0.3 MPa. However, the main\nevents in the sequence exhibit a stress drop larger than the average value.\nFinally, the small seismic efficiency indicates a stress overshoot, possibly\ndue to dynamic effects or large frictional efficiency.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Nov 2018 20:35:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Mar 2019 19:11:15 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 28 Apr 2019 17:57:24 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 30 Apr 2019 10:02:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-06"}
