cted directions close to some of <110>. The large static ADP\ncomponents of LunatB12 are surprisingly combined with high conductivity of the\ncrystal. One may suppose the static shifts (defects) are centers of pinning\nfacilitating formation of additional conductive channels.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Nov 2018 15:51:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-16"}
